                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d555">
                <head>No. 556.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wallace</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-06-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 30, 1883</date>. (Received July
                        16.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 241.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The dragoman of the legation reports this morning
                    that the minister of the interior, who has charge of the business of the
                    petroleum concession, promises to order the prefect of the city to return to the
                        <hi rend="italic">status quo ante</hi>. The formality waited for is a note
                    to the grand vizier to that effect from the minister of foreign affairs.* * * I
                    have directed the dragoman to wait upon the minister of foreign affairs, lest,
                    in the multitude of pressing demands that beset him, his highness may forget to
                    write the note.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>LEW. WALLACE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
